Sometimes in life, if you search too hard, you may not notice that what you need is right in front of you. Maybe, if you allow yourself to let go, it will all fall into place. And maybe, if you bring a sheet of googly eyes, it will help. 
Mexico has been way too good to me. Way more than I could have expected. 
I got a kitten (I think). I learned how to tattoo. I sent some soft rigs. I sweat in the canyon. Y tambien, hablé español con muchas gente, todos los días. Es muy fantastico. I have lent a lot of my time to loving those around me, soaking in the warm waves of friendship and companionship, melting, dancing, laughing. 
Im not ready to leave. Love you, Mexico.

.
..
Jon sending Ego Lounge, third go, in completely goof style. Wearing @tephrahandmade and siq pineapple shorts. We can all learn from this climber drip.

Mexico was magical. Heres a photo dump. Thankful🤍 heart full🌱
To everyone I met: thank you for showing me kindness and goofiness, Im stoked to have new friends and to have spent a lot of time with older friends. 
I have a lot of thoughts on my time there but rather than share them now while they are bonks, Ill just say: sorry for the Irish goodbye, I hope to see and hug you all soon!

This is Duchess. She is a thicccc gurl Cane Toad (Rhinella marina). They are considered the largest speciest in the Family Bufonidae, and Im sure you can see why. They have these huge glands called Parotid glands, swellings on each shoulder you can sort of see (her lovely lady lumps). The toxins secreted are called ‘Bufotoxins’, aptly named from the toads family. If ingested, you, a human, can die. They can release these toxins if threatened, so while you may be temped to kiss her (I MEAN LOOK AT THE FACE!) you very well, should not. Cane Toads are toxic at all stages of life, but honestly, theyre so polite. She really tolerated me holding her for awhile. Once they said I could hold her, I turned around as fast as possible to get gloves as they said “if you want to.” WHY WOULD I SAY NO!? 
Im enjoying my Master Herpetology Course from @amphibianfoundation ! 
Thank you so much, for your time and sharing your knowledge with me, and for all the really amazing and important work you do. Im so thankful for the visit I was gifted. 
If you, like me, love these cuties and other amphibians/ reptiles (all things Herps!), you can take a course as well. Check out @amphibianfoundation and their website. Theyre doing really great work. 
Swipe to see more of duchess and pure joy. I think I look goofy as heck but Duchess is a gem and should be celebrated.✨💘

Well, I finally went to Turkey and it did not disappoint. The climbing is amazing, the food is always fresh, the Turkish people are kind and accomodating, hitch hiking is safe and normal, you get to hear over six languages during breakfast, the views are amazing, the wildlife is awesome(and diverse!), the people and sweet (and silly!), and overall 10/10 want to go back again. What a beautiful experience. 
This photo was taken the day after my birthday sending 36 pitches, (35+1 for good luck), I somehow flashed this route, Saxafon, with help of friends and pure love of this sport. Tufa climbing is so neat! I have a lot to learn. If youre in Geyikbayiri, get on this climb! Its fun 3D, goofy rompin. 
I’ll write more about my time there, but, not spending time on my phone when Im not working has been super good for my brain. Feelin present and grateful.
Thanks for reading💖

When I was young I wanted to write. To write about the dark and the sad and the pain that is the human experience. As an adult, I still find catharsis in writing. I feel less like I want to share my pain and more that I want to share beauty. Joy, warmth, small moments. We ebb and flow through this life and we can only hold tightly to those moments that make us feel more alive. Most inspired. Most full. Full of love and gratitude.
I just want to live.

Anonymous letter part 789:
.
When I first met you, you came into my work. Into my world. And into my heart.
We would laugh so much and stay up way too late, we would make the moon jealous. 
Okay, maybe not that dramatic.
. 
I smoked a pack a day. It was a time where my body didnt need taking care of because my mind and heart were already ruined.
.
.
You saw me. I didnt. You drove me around the city for hours. We cried. You showed me what true love of someone is. To care that much. To intevene that heavily. To say, I see your pain, I am showing up.
.
.
I couldnt be there for you like you were for me. You didnt ask me to. Your selflessness was a big part of who you are. Sometimes it broke you down.
.
When I first met you, I didnt know I needed you.
You saved me. I never thanked you.
.
.
We fell away. I never forgot you. 
You recently reached out. 
Its funny how we project ends, to always be a fault of our own. I, thinking you hated me, you, thinking I was mad at you.
Neither is truer than the other.
My love for you has always been the most wholesome love of that of a sister unborn to the same mother. 
.
.
Your caring and love has always been why people are drawn to you. 
I am grateful to have known that love, I am proud of the woman you have become.
. . . .

Hey friends!
Ive been thinking about this for a couple years and I think its finally time to figure it out and and get the gears turning.
Next Summer (2024- exact dates TBD)
Join me (im bananas) and other rad folks for a pretty intense but pretty awesome trip. 
This post (along with my recent stories) is to gain traction (pun) and interest for something like this. 
This is very early days and it will probably evolve over time. 
The idea:
Bike road& gravel to climbing areas. 
Hike, bike, camp & climb, snack, sleep, laugh, probably wont shower a lot. make memories. Suffer, ache, more snacks, whip, clip, punt, sleep more.
The Route:
Ideally - begin in the grand Tetons, head east ten sleep, lander, finish around spear fish SD.
There is talk of PNW as well, perhaps start or end in Squamish. 
The time committment: 
Four weeks. Three week of travel and activities with a one week allowance for set backs and weather windows.
The price:
YIKES! This is fully in the works. Stay tuned as we gather up info on Van rental access, sponsors for gear (ropes, draws, bikes, helmets etc).
Experience:
This isnt a guided trip as far as, no one is teaching you how toclimb / clean or how gears work on a bike- that said, you dont have to be a triathlete or a 5.13 climber. Abilities welcome experience preferred!
What you need:
Time and stoke.
What to do now?
Please comment below of interest in some wild ride like this.
Interest ≠ committment. It just lets me know who to follow up with. If youre not into the biking part but want to be our van driver, let me know as well. (Seriously)
This has been a big exciting thing in my brain forever. I couldnt understand how more people werent doing this.
This is just putting the idea out there, its not full-on “we are doing this”.
Also to note, the van is there for us for:
Injuries (hopefully none)
Fatigue, not feelin like it, flats and bike issues, and bad weather.
Dont feel intimidated! We likely wont be doing 80+ miles a day, its preferred to keep is less insane as a daily ride and we can drive specific legs that are less ideal/more traffic. 
Comment below “🚲vroom vroom” with interest in being kept in touch! THANK YOU SO MUCH!

Let ur haters b ur motivators

I dont care for spray much but a pretty silly arbitrary goal of mine has been to send 100 5.12s. I knew eventually id get there but, I wanted to really dive into it this last year.
 Id always get distracted by other things, or take time away from outdoors over the summer etc. basically, I didnt really make headway until this last year where I was trying for more volume and hard onsight attempts, second goes etc. 
it has honestly made me love climbing more, as projecting goes, it makes me weak if thats all I am doing, and less well rounded, and well, i unlearn how to fight for chains.
ANYWHEYZ
This goal has been a fucking blast and Im pretty gosh darn proud. Im still weak dont get me wrong, but stoked.
Anyway! I have a whole nerdy spreadsheet of my ticks but wanted to share some of my favorites!
I wont include grades because as my personal grades differ sometimes, Im not interested to hear how you disagree. Some were hard as f. Some were not. Some I have climbed over 50 times because its funz to repeat.
Below are my top ten all time favorite 5.12s from my list of 100 5.12 sends.
Get on them!
If youre cool and want more from the list, I might share, just ask!
In random order:

1. Esplanada //Ten Sleep WY// Grasshopper Wall (photo above)
2. Blue hotel // -Geyikbairyi Turkey// Mevlana
3. Orange juice //- Red River Gorge, KY// Funk Rock City
4. Narcisuss //New River Gorge WV// Summersville Lake
5. Gravy train //Ten Sleep WY// Downtown
6. Zalia //Geyikbairiyi Turkey// Sarkit
7. Inglorious Basterds //El Potrero Chico, Mexico// TNT Wall
8. From beneath you, it devours //Squamich BC// Forgotten Wall
9. Mercy, the huff //Red River Gorge KY// Left Flank
10. Skinny love //Red River Gorge KY//Bob Marley 

Thx for reading, belaying, sharing laughs and being cool cats.
Go climb rocks and just have fun, ya chuffers.
Next goal?? Love side quests.
